ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Form used/assessment name
How much did you talk to the other player?
How much did the other player talk to you?
Participant: How balanced was the conversation? In other words, did both players talk the same amount or did one player talk more than the other?
Notes: 1=Both players talked the same amount; 3=One player talked moderately more; 5=One player dominated the conversation

ElementDescription: How positive or negative were the things that you said during the game?
How positive or negative were the things that the other player said during the game?
Were the things that you said to the other player about the game or about other, unrelated topics?
Notes: 1=Mostly unrelated to the game; 5=Mostly related to the game

ElementDescription: Were the things that the other player said to you about the game or about other, unrelated topics?
Notes: 1=Mostly unrelated to the game; 5=Mostly related to the game

ElementDescription: Participant: How would you rate the overall conversation?
How much did player A talk to player B?
How much did player B talk to player A?
Observer: How balanced was the conversation? In other words, did both players talk about the same amount or did one player talk more than the other?
Notes: 1=Both players talked the same amount; 3=One player talked moderately more; 5=One player dominated the conversation

ElementDescription: How positive or negative were the things that player A said during the game?
How positive or negative were the things that player B said during the game?
Were the things that player A said about the game or about other, unrelated topics?
Notes: 1=Mostly unrelated to the game; 5=Mostly related to the game

ElementDescription: Were the things that player B said about the game or about other, unrelated topics?
Notes: 1=Mostly unrelated to the game; 5=Mostly related to the game

ElementDescription: Observer: How would you rate the overall conversation between the players?
Timepoint/visit label
